Privacy Policy for Bud Pulse

Effective Date: 9/15/2024

1. Introduction

Bud Pulse ("we", "our", "us") values the privacy of its users ("you", "your"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when you use the Bud Pulse mobile application ("App").

By using our App, you agree to the collection and use of your data in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the practices described in this policy, please do not use the App.

2. Information We Collect

We may collect the following information:

Personal Data: We do not collect personally identifiable information such as name, email, or contact details unless you provide them to us voluntarily.

Plant Data: Data entered by users such as plant health, watering schedules, and other plant-related information will be stored locally on your device and will not be shared or uploaded to our servers.

App Usage Data: We may collect anonymized data about how the App is used to improve the user experience. This may include information such as the type of mobile device you use, your device's unique ID, IP address, operating system, and usage statistics.

3. How We Use Your Information

The information we collect is used to:

Improve and personalize your experience in the App.
Provide customer support.
Analyze app usage to improve features.
4. Data Storage and Security

Your plant data is stored locally on your device and is not uploaded to any external servers. We do not collect or store any sensitive personal information. We implement security measures to protect the data stored on your device. However, no method of electronic storage is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Sharing Your Information

We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal data to outside parties. Your information is stored locally on your device and is not shared with any third-party services unless required by law.

6. Third-Party Services

Bud Pulse does not integrate with any third-party services that collect or process user data.

7. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

Our App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under the age of 13. If we learn that we have collected personal data from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. You are advised to review this policy periodically for any changes. Continued use of the App after changes to the policy will signify your acceptance of the changes.

9. Contact Us

